<br>
Get in groups where you (the wiz) is used for more than a taxi. Thats up to play style not our ablilities. For example, Im maxed out in all my combat skills and habitually have a speed and Howler on from our chanters. Its pretty interesting and effective to go melee a mob that wont just die off the top and do 1-2k damage on top of your DD. This is against everything you are taught about wizzies and it works like a charm. Spend that 215 mana for the draught or just whack a sub 20 critter til it dies?<br>
<br>
Or the converse is true - be the puller for the group. With jboots and a Floox Staff we are marvelous pullers. In a fit of boredom some months ago I pulled for 8 straight hrs at the Burning Woods giant fort. Admittedly I was high enough to solo pull but I was dragging critters out to a party fast enough that they and I both leveled with very little effort at all. Not even a chanter. Just pull em and drop em.<br>
<br>
AE groups are much harder for me to find as we seem to have more chanters than we know what to do with. My chanters wont C2 me if I break their rez. So its a delecate task to drop a pillar that will kill one and whack on the other 1/2 of a normal pull.<br>
<br>
Finally, there are things that could be done to enhance the class but what we have asked for isnt it so far. Any suggestion that has the word &quot;solo&quot; in it should be ignored. Soloing sucks. <br>
