I didn't learn to quad because I had to, I did it because it's a lot of fun.  I love the challenge of it, the skill and finesse of getting the four baddies to drop.  Especially the first time I pull a new set of mobs I have never quaded before.  The same is true for AoE groups.  I don't do them because I have to, I have lots of friends that I do regular groups with.  I do AoE because it's the best times you can have in the game.  Killing Trak or Zland is fun, but not very personal, takes too many people to feel like it was you who did the killing.  But, an AoE group functions like clockwork, laying down 50-75% of every casters mana to take out a pile of mobs.  When the six of you see that 10th mob fall, everyone breathes a sigh and laughs.  It's crazy, very intense, and a lot of fun.<br>
<br>
Wizards are very group friendly in AoE groups.  You should try it.  Half the groups are normally wizzies.  If you can't think outside VI's narrow idea of what a group should be, then you deserve to wallow in your wizzy self-pity.  All the personal attacks on me will not get you into another boring seb group, so what's your point.  I'm pretty sure I laid out how to get out of that hole you keep putting yourself in, so why don't you try it instead of yakking about stuff you can't fix.<br>
<br>
Now for Grim's post:<br>
<br>
I keep saying that being in a regular group is pointless to begin with, so why do you keep bringing it up?  The answer to your grouping problem isn't quad, it's AoE.  Quad is for solo action, AoE for group, don't confuse the two remedies.  Your problem with my solution seems to be based on your lack of effort to even attempt it.  The only reason more people don't AoE group is because nobody takes the time to try it.  Once people do AoE groups, nothing else will make them happy.  The exps you get from AoE are 2-3 times what a normal group can make and a heck of a lot more fun.  You can't quad frogs in seb, but two AoE groups in seb can burn down every frog from the bar and chef in 45 secs.  Other camps used to howl at us for taking all the critters because every 3-5 mins we needed another dozen to torch.  Our personal best pull was 17 critters in one pull (with two groups).  I'd love to hear of others beating our record.<br>
<br>
Quading isn't an aberration, it's a tactic.  Why sit in one spot all day and easily burn down one thing at a time when you can sit in one spot and kill four at a time?  You can quad in any outdoor zone with the spells we have.  There isn't one wizard who is good at quad that would ever go back to solo pulls.  I've quaded in SK, EK, OOT, TD, BW, SF, and DL.  I quaded so many guards, they nerfed them, but I figured out a way to quad them anyway (they raised the MR so BoF wouldn't stick, but I could still outrun them with jboots by just enough).<br>
<br>
What's normal anyway?  2 years ago I was a heretic for saying you could quad kite.  Now, every class with a good AoE and snare does it.  Probably everyone reading these boards has seen some wizzy or druid doing it.  Wasn't &quot;normal&quot; two years ago to kite that way, but it is now.  Only thing that changed was people listened and tried it.  The same will be true with AoE grouping.  Sure, now it sounds almost mystical, but it happens all the time.  The only thing keeping it from being the &quot;normal&quot; way to group is people trying it.  Just like solo folks who quad won't go back to single kiting, AoE folks will want to AoE all the time.<br>
<br>
As far as balance goes, AoE groups gain exps 2-3 times as fast as a standard group.  If anything, wizard dominant AoE groups are too powerful, but I'm not saying anything to VI and I doubt anyone who does AoE will.  The only drawback to AoE was always making the other exp camps mad from taking all the spawns, but AoE is very efficient.<br>
<br>
Now, for the last section of the my last post in this thread.<br>
<br>
So it comes down to what wizards are willing to do.  Some will just sit back and write the never-ending gripe to VI and cry them a river hoping VI will change something so we'll fit better into their &quot;vision&quot; of groups.  Others, like me, will figure out a much better way to level and have fun.  If VI ever gave wizards something to make them fit into a stadard group, I still wouldn't do them.  They are too boring and the exps are way too slow.  Hey, it's your 10 bucks a month, if you want to beg to get into a group for your money, who am I to stop you?  As for me, I expect some good times for my cash, whether VI likes it or not.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 5:30:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This board always crack me up...</span><hr size=1> You will get no argument from me on the fun of the AoE group.  The only problem on my server is, there aren't enough people willing to put the time in to learn.  They happen so rarely that it is discouraging to even try.  I mean, I WILL keep trying, but that is the problem.  There just isn't enough interest.  Which I find interesting because it is BY FAR the most exciting aspect of the game for ANY class.  (taking out MAJOR mob raids which sometimes not very desirable.)<br>
