<br>
I can give you several reasons.<br>
<br>
1) You can't really do good AE grouping every level, in fact until level 20 Enchanters only have one AE stun, and mes isn't especially useful for this.<br>
2) AE spells are scattered through levels and not consistently useful.<br>
3) Not everywhere can sustain AE blasting<br>
4) This is not a tactic 90% of the public can or wants to do<br>
5) AE grouping isn't possible in many of the places people like to hunt or for things people like to get<br>
6) This game isn't about my needs and desires it is a grouping game, I can't force everyone to play one way just to make me happy or fit in<br>
7) AE Groupin is just as unusual and non standard as the usual group and as such fits in the quad-kiting concept.<br>
<br>
I like AE as much as the next, more than most.  You should know by now that I am one of its biggest supporters and proponents.  The problem is, most Wizards even don't like it and are scared of it.  How, precisely, can you expect the game and the classes to be balanced by something like this?<br>
<br>
Saying &quot;go do AE&quot; isn't the solution, and Verant recognizes this.  They are working on other things for the class, because they understand that isn't the answer.  Don't dismiss peoples' concerns about this because you can get into regular AE groups, that's not standard in any remotest sense of the word for this game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqwade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 10:23:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hey Nizzdal</span><hr size=1> Actually the population of Clerics/Chanters willing to do AoE is growing on Lanys.  One good AoE group is all it takes to hook em in.   <p><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=10459><b>Qwade Starlifter</b></a><BR>
