<a href=http://www.seven-dreams.org/><i>Seven Dreams</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 11:04:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tactics fail without other wizards</span><hr size=1> The other issue is the lack of wizards available, period.  On The Nameless, there have been many times when I'll look around the zone, and there are less than 3 wizards total.  I'll look around OS, check Trakon's Teeth, wizards are nowhere to be found.  <br>
<br>
So, no wizards means AoE groups are suicide.  Wizards AoE and cast MUCH faster than the other classes and because of it, on the &quot;boss mobs&quot;, it takes multiple wizards.<br>
<br>
That's the key to our problem, wizards become stronger the more of us there are, but by ourselves, we end up with problems.  Form a group, make sure there's two instead of one wizard, and watch the mobs drop so quickly the tanks blink in surprise.  Do this consistantly, the wizards don't end up out of mana, the mobs drop very quickly, and people scratch their heads.<br>
<br>
Tanks can do well in a group without other tanks as long as they have enchanter and cleric support.<br>
<br>
Clerics do well in a group because the other classes need their heals.<br>
<br>
Wizards need other wizards, and one enchanter to be the power people see in the class.  A single wizard in a group doesn't have the mana to cast frequently enough to take down mob after mob when in a group.  Two wizards, even without AoE tactics will drop 10k hit point mobs VERY fast, and because they share the agro with the tank(s), generally have fewer agro problems when chain casting.  Our strength is when we work together, and perhaps the best solution is to push for two wizards to a group.  In raids, when the call to nuke comes, it's the power of multiple wizards that drop the mob quickly enough to avoid agro.  If it's a single wizard pumping lures into the mob, the wizard dies from overagro since the mob doesn't die fast enough.<br>
